  <title>Math 150  Activity 29: Critical points</title>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Identify the critical points of the functions <m>h(t)</m> and <m>k(t)</m> in each of the figures below.
        Each function's derivative appears below it.
      </p>
      <image>
        <latex-image>
          <![CDATA[\begin{tikzpicture}\begin{axis}[
          xlabel=\(t\),
          ylabel=\(h(t)\),
          xmin=0, xmax=6,
          ymin=-10, ymax=10,
          minor x tick num = 4,
          minor y tick num = 3,
          width=0.35\linewidth,
          grid=major,
          ]
          \addplot[domain=0:6, style=very thick] {-1*(x-4)^2+2};
          \end{axis}\end{tikzpicture}]]>
        </latex-image>
      </image>
      <image>
        <latex-image>
          <![CDATA[\begin{tikzpicture}\begin{axis}[
