  <exercise workspace=".70%">
    <statement>
      <p>
        The oxygen supply, <m>S</m>,
        in blood depends on the hematocrit,
        <m>H</m> (the percentage of red blood cells in the blood):
        <me>
          S = aHe^{-bH}  \text{ where \(a\) and \(b\) are positive constants. }
        </me>
      </p>

      <p>
        What values of <m>H</m> maximize and minimize (respectively) the oxygen supply?
        Your answers may include some <m>a</m>s and <m>b</m>s.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <pagebreak />

  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        On the graphs of <m>f'(x)</m> and <m>g'(x)</m> shown below,
        give the <m>x</m>-coordinates of all critical points of <m>f(x)</m> and <m>g(x)</m> and identify them as local maxima, local minima,
        or neither.
      </p>
      <image>
        <latex-image>
          <![CDATA[\begin{tikzpicture}\begin{axis}[
          xlabel=\(x\),
          ylabel=\(f'(x)\),
          xmin=-2, xmax=6,
          ymin=-4, ymax=6,
          minor x tick num = 3,
          minor y tick num = 3,
          width=0.35\linewidth,
          grid=major,
          ]
          \addplot[domain=-2:6, style=very thick] {(x-3)^2 - 2};
          \end{axis}\end{tikzpicture}]]>
        </latex-image>
      </image>
      <image>
        <latex-image>
          <![CDATA[\begin{tikzpicture}\begin{axis}[
          xlabel=\(x\),
